at":"2019-10-13T09:43:05.144Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"I. Summary\nAdobe Flash Player is prone to a vulnerability which leads to Memory Corruption. \n------------------------------------------------------------------\nII. Description\nWhen ASnative(101,10) is called with a MovieClip object pointer, Flash Player is crashed due to an invalid EIP value. Carefully crafted swf file may allow the attacker to hijack the EIP, leading to shellcode execution in the context of affected application. \n\nLastest version of Adobe Flash Player 20.0.0.267 has been tested under Windows 7.\n------------------------------------------------------------------\nIII. Impact\nMemory Corruption\n------------------------------------------------------------------\nIV. Credit\nWen Guanxing from Venustech ADLAB is credited for this vulnerability.\n\nIt has been assigned as CVE-2016-0981 by Adobe.\nhttps://helpx.adobe.com/security/products/flash-player/apsb16-04.html\n","bounty_amount":"5000.0","formatted_bounty":"$5,000","weakness":{"id":2,"name":"Memory Corruption - Generic"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[{"id":76001,"file_name":"crash.swf","expiring_url":"https://hackerone-us-west-2-production-attachments.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/000/076/001/627e80be7a23ebf114aaaf12e533cfafdbe23776/crash.swf?response-content-disposition=attachment%3B%20filename%3D%22crash.swf%22%3B%20filename%2A%3DUTF-8%27%27crash.swf\u0026response-content-type=application%2Foctet-stream\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=ASIAQGK6FURQYJPM5INV%2F20260429%2Fus-west-2%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20260429T091600Z\u0026X-Amz-Expires=3600\u0026X-Amz-Security-Token=IQoJb3JpZ2luX2VjECgaCXVzLXdlc3QtMiJGMEQCIGPTFP%2F%2B61NRXKxUCRRiOEw%2FyEXMoJI30jSWgewoYzlYAiATW70r0%2Ft4BCmx%2BIRRvI9N9Vm6tq25cJqmqyf8P9oJnSq6BQjx%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F8BEAMaDDAxMzYxOTI3NDg0OSIMlnlVa%2Fn%2F5%2FBwcq%2Bd